{
  "schema_version": "2.7.0",
  "name": "pn_1d_pulse",
  "description": "1D pn diode switching transient: anode bias steps from 0.0 V to 0.6 V at t = 5 ns via the M16.7 voltage_t.step variant. Geometry mirrors pn_1d_turnon (20 um symmetric step junction, N_A = N_D = 1e17 cm^-3, tau = 1e-7 s, 800 cells). The pre-step current is order-of-magnitude smaller than the post-step current. The verifier (scripts/run_benchmark.py verify_pn_1d_pulse) asserts I(t) is finite everywhere, the pre-step current is order-of-magnitude smaller than the post-step current, and the post-step current at t = 50 ns matches the pn_1d_turnon final-time current within 20 %. Demonstration benchmark; the formal V&V gate for voltage_t lives in tests/audit/test_06_transient_fft_vs_ac_sweep.py.",
